Born and raised in the prairies, Kandis Friesen is an artist and cultural worker based in Montr&eacute;al, Qu&eacute;bec. Working from an interdisciplinary approach to both drawing and moving image, her work has been shown locally and internationally at various festivals and galleries, including recent projects with DARE-DARE and OBORO in Montreal, Mural Arts Program / Broken City Lab (Philadelphia, US), and Eastern Edge (St. John&#39;s, CA), and recent screenings at VIVO Media Arts (Coast Salish Territories / Vancouver, CA), Athens Digital Arts Festival (Athens, GR), and Traverse Vid&eacute;o (Toulouse, FR). She has been the recipient of several grants and awards, and has participated in the residencies Neighborhood Time Exchange in Philadelphia (2015), OBORO&rsquo;s Residencies for Local Artists Program in Montreal (2015), and an upcoming residency at MAWA in Winnipeg (2016).

&nbsp;

As a cultural worker, her teaching frameworks are informed by feminist and artist-run culture, blending theoretical and hands-on experience to create open and accessible spaces that encourage self-determined learning and cultural expression. Her technical labour has included technical direction, art handling and gallery installation, maintenance, administration, audio and video post/production, and live technician work in theatre, music, film/video, and arts venues. She has developed and facilitated workshops in diverse contexts &ndash; artist-run, incarcerated, academic, DIY, and other community spaces &ndash; in Canada and the U.S., teaching on the subjects of DIY electronics, contact microphones and sound art, drawing, experimental animation and moving image, and the realm of copyright, ethics, and appropriation of the image in contemporary arts production.

&nbsp;

bodyfrench:
N&eacute;e et &eacute;lev&eacute;e dans les Prairies, Kandis Friesen est une artiste et travailleuse culturelle bas&eacute;e &agrave; Montr&eacute;al, Qu&eacute;bec. Elle travaille &agrave; partir d&#39;une approche interdisciplinaire, m&ecirc;lant &agrave; la fois dessin et image en mouvement. Son travail a &eacute;t&eacute; pr&eacute;sent&eacute; localement et &agrave; l&rsquo;international dans divers festivals et galeries, incluant ses projets r&eacute;cents avec DARE-DARE et OBORO &agrave; Montr&eacute;al, Mural Arts Program / Broken City Lab (Philadelphie, &Eacute;-U), et Eastern Edge (St. John&#39;s, CA), ainsi que ses plus r&eacute;centes projections pr&eacute;sent&eacute;es &agrave; VIVO Media Arts (Coast Salish Territories / Vancouver, CA), Athens Digital Arts Festival (Ath&egrave;nes, GR), et &agrave; Traverse Vid&eacute;o (Toulouse, FR). Elle est r&eacute;cipiendaire de plusieurs prix et bourses et a particip&eacute; &agrave; plusieurs r&eacute;sidences dont Neighborhood Time Exchange &agrave; Philadelphie (2015) ainsi que le programme de r&eacute;sidences des artistes locaux d&rsquo;OBORO (2015). Sa prochaine r&eacute;sidence d&rsquo;artiste se d&eacute;roulera &agrave; MAWA &agrave; Winnipeg (2016).

En tant que travailleuse culturelle, elle s&rsquo;inspire de mod&egrave;les bas&eacute;s sur la culture f&eacute;ministe et des centres d&rsquo;artistes, m&ecirc;lant exp&eacute;rience th&eacute;orique et pratique pour cr&eacute;er des espaces ouverts et accessibles qui encouragent l&#39;apprentissage autog&eacute;r&eacute; et l&#39;expression culturelle. Son travail en technique inclut la direction technique, la manipulation d&rsquo;&oelig;uvres, l&#39;installation en galerie, la maintenance, l&#39;administration, la production et postproduction vid&eacute;o et audio, ainsi que le travail de technicienne lors d&rsquo;&eacute;v&eacute;nements (dans les milieux du th&eacute;&acirc;tre, de la musique, du cin&eacute;ma, et dans plusieurs salles de spectacle). Elle a d&eacute;velopp&eacute; et anim&eacute; des ateliers dans divers contextes &ndash; centres d&#39;artistes autog&eacute;r&eacute;s, milieux carc&eacute;raux, universitaires, DIY et autres espaces communautaires &ndash; au Canada et aux &Eacute;tats-Unis, basant son enseignement sur les sujets du bricolage &eacute;lectronique, de l&#39;art sonore, du dessin, de l&#39;animation exp&eacute;rimentale et des images en mouvement, mais aussi sur le droit d&#39;auteur, l&#39;&eacute;thique, et l&#39;appropriation de l&#39;image dans la production artistique contemporaine.

&nbsp;
